#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "[[!meta title=\"Managing passwords using KeePassXC\"]]\n"
msgid "[[!meta title=\"Managing passwords using the Secrets password manager\"]]\n"
msgstr "[[!meta title=\"Passwortverwaltung mit KeePassXC\"]]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Using the [*KeePassXC*](https://keepassxc.org/)  password manager you can:"
msgid ""
"Using the [*Secrets*](https://apps.gnome.org//Secrets/)  password manager "
"you can:"
msgstr ""
"Mithilfe des Passwortmanagers [*KeePassXC*](https://keepassxc.org/) können "
"Sie:"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Store many passwords in an encrypted database which is protected by a "
#| "single passphrase of your choice."
msgid ""
"Store many passwords in an encrypted database, called a *safe*, which is "
"protected by a single passphrase of your choice."
msgstr ""
"Viele Passwörter in einer verschlüsselten Datenbank speichern, die durch "
"eine Passphrase Ihrer Wahl geschützt ist."

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Always use different and stronger passwords, since you only have to "
#| "remember a single passphrase to unlock the entire database."
msgid ""
"Always use different and stronger passwords, because you only have to "
"remember a single passphrase to unlock the entire safe."
msgstr ""
"Immer unterschiedliche und stärkere Passwörter verwenden, da Sie sich nur an "
"die Passphrase zum Entsperren der Datenbank erinnern müssen."

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "- Generate very strong random passwords."
msgid "Generate very strong random passwords."
msgstr "- Sehr starke zufällige Passwörter generieren."

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "- Generate one-time verification codes for two-factor authentication."
msgid "Generate one-time verification codes for two-factor authentication."
msgstr "- Generate one-time verification codes for two-factor authentication."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<div class=\"note\">\n"
msgstr "<div class=\"note\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In Tails 7.6 (March 2026), we replaced the\n"
"<i>[[KeePassXC|https://keepassxc.org/]]</i> password manager with\n"
"<i>Secrets</i>.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>You can open your previous <i>KeePassXC</i> database using <i>Secrets</i>,\n"
"because both <i>Secrets</i> and <i>KeePassXC</i> use the same file format to\n"
"store passwords.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>If you miss more advanced features from <i>KeePassXC</i>, you can install\n"
"<i>KeePassXC</i> as [[additional\n"
"software|persistent_storage/additional_software]]</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "</div>\n"
msgstr "</div>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "<h1 id=\"create\">Creating and saving a password database</h1>\n"
msgid "<h1 id=\"create\">Creating and saving a password safe</h1>\n"
msgstr "<h1 id=\"create\">Eine Passwortdatenbank erstellen und speichern</h1>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Follow these steps to create a new password database and save it in the "
#| "Persistent Storage for use in future working sessions."
msgid ""
"Follow these steps to create a new password safe and save it in the "
"Persistent Storage for use in future working sessions."
msgstr ""
"Befolgen Sie diese Schritte, um eine neue Passwortdatenbank zu erstellen und "
"sie im beständigen Datenspeicher zu speichern, damit sie in zukünftigen "
"Arbeitssitzungen verwendet werden kann."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To learn how to create a Persistent Storage, read our [[documentation on the "
"Persistent Storage|persistent_storage]]."
msgstr ""
"Um zu erfahren, wie man einen persistenten Speicher erstellt, lesen Sie "
"unsere [[Dokumentation zum persistenten Speicher|persistent_storage]]."

#. type: Bullet: '0. '
msgid "When starting Tails, unlock the Persistent Storage."
msgstr "Beim Starten von Tails den beständigen Datenspeicher entsperren."

#. type: Bullet: '0. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "In Tails, choose **Applications**&nbsp;▸ **Persistent Storage**."
